Gets order summaries matching the filter criteria. Filters are passed as a URI parameter in the format <Field>.<Operator>=<Value>. For example, /order-summaries?FirstName.CN=Matt or /order-summaries?FirstName.EQ=John&LastName.EQ=Doe

Operation orderSummarySearchOrders

public orderSummarySearchOrders(string $customer_number[, string $filter_search = null ][, DateTime $filter_begin_date = null ][, DateTime $filter_end_date = null ][, bool $filter_exclude_backorder_fufillment = null ][, bool $filter_exclude_premium_fill = null ][, string $filter_membership_organization = null ][, array<string|int, string> $filter_owning_organizations = null ][, bool $filter_is_posted = null ][, bool $filter_has_product_order_line = null ][, bool $filter_is_in_status_that_allows_modifications = null ][, int $pager_skip = null ][, int $pager_take = null ]) : SearchResultWithCountOrderSummary

Get all past orders for a given customer, that match the searchAgument. The result of those orders can be limited to N at a time. The list starts with the newest orders.

Parameters
$customer_number : string

The Advantage customer number of the bill-to customer on the orders. (required)

$filter_search : string = null

The generic search argument. (Typically from a search text box). This term will be compared to several fields on the order. (optional)

$filter_begin_date : DateTime = null

The beginning date. Only orders placed after this date will be returned. (optional)

$filter_end_date : DateTime = null

The end date. Only orders placed before this date will be returned. (optional)

$filter_exclude_backorder_fufillment : bool = null

Exclude backorder-fulfillment orders (optional)

$filter_exclude_premium_fill : bool = null

Exclude premium-fill orders (optional)

$filter_membership_organization : string = null

Membership organization to filter by (optional)

$filter_owning_organizations : array<string|int, string> = null

Owning organizations to filter by (optional)

$filter_is_posted : bool = null

Order's posting status. Filter orders based on whether or not the order is posted. (optional)

$filter_has_product_order_line : bool = null

Filter orders based on whether or not the order has a product order line. (optional)

$filter_is_in_status_that_allows_modifications : bool = null

Filter orders based on whether or not the order is in a status that allows further modification (optional)

$pager_skip : int = null

The number of records to skip. (optional)

$pager_take : int = null

The number of records to return. (optional)
